This paper proposes a convolutional neural network for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The network architecture incorporates attention mechanisms and residual learning, which are also popular topics in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
